            <ul>
              <li>Genuinely scales to 50M+ URLs without breaking</li>
              <li>Best-in-class JavaScript rendering at scale</li>
              <li>Scheduled crawls + Looker / Tableau exports</li>
              <li>Team workflow (assign, comment, resolve) actually works</li>
              <li>Log file integration is a real differentiator</li>
              <li>SOC 2 Type II + ISO 27001 — enterprise-procurement-friendly</li>
              <li>Strong customer success team (named CSM on Corporate+)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="cons-card">
            <h4>✗ Where it hurts</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Pricing is opaque and high — minimum ~$14K/year</li>
              <li>247 issue types is overwhelming for new users</li>
              <li>UI feels dated next to Sitebulb or Ahrefs Site Audit</li>
              <li>No native rank tracking — you still need Ahrefs or Semrush</li>
              <li>No content suggestions — pure technical audit only</li>
              <li>Setup takes 2–3 weeks of CSM-led onboarding</li>
              <li>Annual contract only — no monthly trial</li>
            </ul>
