        <h2 id="alternatives">Top 7 DeepCrawl alternatives</h2>
        <p>If $14K/year is out of reach (it is for most teams), here are the seven crawlers we tested side-by-side, ranked by best fit.</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>theStacc</strong> — $49/mo. Audit + content + GBP + ranks in one. <a href="/checkout/">Start $1 trial →</a></li>
          <li><strong>Screaming Frog</strong> — £239/year. The desktop classic. Best for one-off audits under 500K URLs.</li>
          <li><strong>Sitebulb</strong> — $35/mo. Best visualisations of any crawler. Excellent for agency reports.</li>
          <li><strong>Ahrefs Site Audit</strong> — included with any Ahrefs plan. Great if you already pay for Ahrefs.</li>
          <li><strong>JetOctopus</strong> — $99/mo. The price/performance sweet spot above 100K URLs.</li>
          <li><strong>OnCrawl</strong> — from $250/mo. Strong log file integration. Smaller than Lumar but cheaper.</li>
          <li><strong>Botify</strong> — Lumar's closest enterprise competitor. Similar price, similar feature set.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Quick example: equivalent Lumar config in Screaming Frog</h3>
        <p>If you are evaluating a downgrade, here is the Screaming Frog CLI command that replicates a basic scheduled audit:</p>

        <div class="code-block">
          <div class="code-head">
            <span class="dot r"></span><span class="dot y"></span><span class="dot g"></span>
            <span class="name">terminal · screaming-frog audit</span>
          </div>
          <pre><span class="c"># Replace YOUR_SITE and adjust crawl-config.json for auth</span>
ScreamingFrogSEOSpiderCli.sh \
  <span class="k">--crawl</span> <span class="s">"https://yoursite.com/"</span> \
  <span class="k">--config</span> <span class="s">"./crawl-config.json"</span> \
  <span class="k">--output-folder</span> <span class="s">"./audits/$(date +%Y-%m-%d)/"</span> \
  <span class="k">--export-format</span> csv \
  <span class="k">--save-crawl</span> \
  <span class="k">--headless</span></pre>
        </div>

        <p>Run that on a nightly cron. Pipe the CSVs into Looker Studio. You have rebuilt 60% of Lumar Monitor for $20/month in cloud compute.</p>

        <div class="divider-rule"><span>—</span></div>

        <h2 id="verdict">Final verdict</h2>
        <p>DeepCrawl (Lumar) is what it claims to be: the most powerful site crawler on the market. If your job description includes the phrase "technical SEO lead" and you own a site above 1M URLs, it is the right tool and the price is justified.</p>

        <p>If you are anyone else — a founder, a marketer, an agency owner with 20 client sites — Lumar is a Ferrari you will park in the garage. Pick a smaller crawler and put the saved $13,000 toward content that ranks.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-success">
          <div class="callout-label">✓ Our recommendation</div>
          <p><strong>For enterprise teams (1M+ URLs, 3+ SEOs):</strong> DeepCrawl / Lumar. Buy the Enterprise tier, skip Corporate.<br><strong>For everyone else:</strong> Start with theStacc ($49/mo) for content + local + audits, or Screaming Frog (£239/yr) for one-off technical audits.</p>
